    "ailments_description": "The most common ailments you can heal with Isodon lasiocarpus are bronchitis, with its essential oils used to reduce inflammation and relieve coughs, and fever, which can be alleviated by its antipyretic properties. Additionally, Isodon lasiocarpus is used to treat respiratory issues such as asthma by reducing inflammation and improving lung function. Its anti-inflammatory properties also make it effective in treating gastrointestinal problems like ulcers and gastritis. Isodon lasiocarpus has been found to have antimicrobial properties, which can aid in the treatment of skin infections like cellulitis and furuncles. Furthermore, its antioxidant properties help to protect against oxidative stress, reducing the risk of diseases like cancer.",
